				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zadimortis" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5350423); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5350423&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="Zadimortis" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5350423)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zadimortis" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5350423); return false;" >Zadimortis</a></span> <span class="odate time_1566866973 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Aug 2019 00:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4341159">
									

<p>I was literally just re-reading the stories in this series when I reloaded the page, saw a new link, and proceeded to lose my shit. This series is phenomenal, it's inspiring me to be better as a writer. +1, +100000 if I could. Thank you for writing this.</p>
<p>With regard to your block-of-text, I think the integration of Ulrich is plenty fine. I'm of the opinion that if it isn't important to a storyline then it's safe to leave out so long as it's consistent, and it's clear that you put a lot of thought into consistency here. Marion deeply influenced many people in her line of work, we don't need to know the life story of every one. You made Ulrich just interesting enough without forcing artificial plot importance on her, and it worked out in my opinion.</p>
<p>Truly excellent work, thank you again for writing all this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
