														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4341261">
									

<p>I gotta admit it, it's come to a bit of a disappointment. Story-wise, you are very much right; not to mention that you're doing this out of respect for Sirpudding's worldbuilding and characters. However, Arà Orún working its way into your canon and then having to cut ties with it so abruptly is definitely a downside. Personally, I would have preferred an approach closer to Dread and Circuses' Iris Dark, who was heavily inspired by Acidverse but it's not the same character. I think the nöosphere and everything involved in it has a lot of potential in your story. I also liked Ulrich and how you were aiming to portray her.</p>
<p>That's enough crying over spilled milk. Now it's time for the good part, as you said.</p>

