														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4341496">
									

<p>I view this as similar to a comic book crossover. You're in the middle of writing an ongoing book about characters you have plans for, and then a requirement shows up to &quot;down tools&quot; briefly and interlock with a different storyline as it passes through yours. It can be disruptive. It can be confusing to a reader who isn't familiar with both stories. But it's part of the job, and being able to deal with that kind of swerve is a necessary skill in this domain. And closure is important and I hate seeing stuff left incomplete, it's the number one thing I try to discourage here.</p>

							</div>

								
					
