				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tombones" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(398766); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=398766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="tombones" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=398766)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tombones" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(398766); return false;" >tombones</a></span> <span class="odate time_1567618520 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Sep 2019 17:35</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4350851">
									

<p>I was just recommending the Antimemetics Divison tales to some friends when I discovered this new entry in my favorite series on the site, posted mere days ago.. as if I'd been discretely reminded to check the division hub by some of our better angels. OoOoOooo</p>
<p>Reading here about the journey you took to finish this is fascinating, because I wouldn't have guessed you had to take on the mantle of the Saints by yourself. You faithfully blended these storylines in a way that I'm sure would make sirpudding proud. You also achieved quite a feat, making sacrifice and loss still feel meaningful in a world that's already gone to hell more horrifically than almost any other Foundation &quot;Bad End&quot; I can think of. I can't fathom anyone making it out alive at this point, but I still can't wait to see them try.</p>
<p>I hope the next entry isn't quite as arduous for you to write, but whenever you get there, I hope some generous Bader-Ramjin Infomorphic Entity will tap me on the shoulder and remind me to check the wiki again. +1</p>

							</div>

								
